Before you can connect Alexa with Midea smart appliance devices, please kindly follow below steps:
1. Download "SmartHome" (formerly MSmartHome) app from Google Play or App Store;
2. Sign up or sign in with your SmartHome (formerly MSmartHome) account;
3. Setup the device with your "SmartHome" (formerly MSmartHome) app, and make sure you can control it by the app;
4. Open Alexa app, search "SmartHome" (formerly MSmartHome) skill and enable it by signing in with the same ID you used in "smartHome"(formerly MSmartHome) app.
5. When setup is ready, try ask Alexa to control your Midea home appliance.
